✨THE LAST REUNION✨

by Kayte Nunn

4/5 stars ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Spanning from the 1940’s during WW11, to the new millennium, 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗟𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝗥𝗲𝘂𝗻𝗶𝗼𝗻 is the story of a group of women who served in the Women’s Axillary Services in the “forgotten war” of the East – in Burma.

It is also the story of newly found friendships in the early days of 2000 as we discover another young woman who is far away from home.

The roles of women before, during and after the war are heavily explored and are at the forefront of this novel.  But there is also homage to Orential art with specific focus on Japanese netsuke – which I personally found fascinating.

Thanks to @tandemcollectiveglobal and @hachetteaus hosting #thelastreunionreadalong we had an amazing live Q&A with @kaytenunn2 which helped me understand the process and ideas behind the novel.

It has been a joy reading a #historicalfiction with an unique setting and storyline.

And the biggest thanks to @byronbayteacompany for the tea! I’m enjoying the ginger zing as we speak!! 

